2.5.2 Installation Environment
The installatio n environment is critical to the robot's performance. The installation environment is as follows:
(1) The flatness deviation of the mounting surface should be controlled within 0.5 mm;
(2) Installation temperature should be between 0°C and 45°C;
(3) Install in an environment with humidity levels between 20% and 80%, ensuring no condensation occurs;
(4) The installation altitude should not exceed 1000 meters;
(5) The pollution category is Class III;
(6) Areas free of flammable or corrosive liquids or gases;
(7) Stay away from locations with strong sources of electrical noise;
(8) Locations without significant impact or vibration.

